Sie flipped to a blank page and noted the date. Below that she wrote „11.5.648–13.12.648“.
„Are you stirring up old memories?“, inquired Ivory and looked at the old notebook. Kari nodded. „Do you think they'll let you out for Christmas? There are only a few days left.“
Kari tapped twice on the lantern. „No“, as Ivory had guessed. The Ice King never let Kari out, for he considered her a „flaw“. She was born deaf and was the only daughter in the family, her siblings were all boys.
Similar was the case with Ivory. When Ivory came out as non-binary, it seemed as if the world would change. As a punishment for this difference, Ivory was given tasks where most of the time she was alone.
Additionally, Ivory was forced to serve the princess. But it didn't bother Ivory much, since Ivory also gained a friend.
„You're having a birthday soon, right?“, asked Ivory, thinking about the fact that the princess was having her birthday in a few days. Kari nodded with a sad flicker in her bright blue eyes.
„Would you like to celebrate your birthday?“, asked Ivory, thinking back to the last time the princess answered this question.
„No“, tapped Kari. Ivory knew this was a difficult topic for her. Her birthday was the day she was locked in this room and her mother was banished. Ivory was still a baby at the time, but she remembered how upset the servants and the citizens of the city had been. Ivory had heard that Eirwen was a popular queen. And that she strangely could predict things that later actually happened.
„Well, what would you like to do?“, asked Ivory. Kari looked at Ivory excitedly. She held a piece of paper in her hand. It read:
15 x 15 cm canvas
Weiß, various shades of blue
Brushes in six different sizes
Easel
“These things should I get for you?” Ivory turned to the silent princess, whose braids swayed back and forth from her vigorous tapping. “Yes?” Ivory giggled softly. The usually reserved princess showed so much excitement. It was the first time she had asked about something that had nothing to do with books and came from outside her room.
“Okay! Let's see each other later?” asked Ivory, stood up and slung through the chaos of paper and notebooks.
Kari nodded, turned back to her notes, and wrapped herself in her blanket.
Ivory left the room, relieved that the princess had finally stepped out of her comfort zone and asked for things beyond her reach, like Malfarben.
Ivory ran through the corridors again and tried to ignore the gossip of the maids.
"I've heard that she is possessed by Queen Eirwen and therefore keeps coming back to this room."
"I've heard that she eats children in this room."
“She looks like a man, that's not normal, is it?”
Ivory covered her ears because she couldn't ignore the gossip any longer, and continued on. The room of the royal painter was in the east wing, behind the second door on the left side.
Ivory approached the door, which was just as intricately decorated as Karis door. On it was the White Dragon, one of the six Original Dragons supposedly responsible for creating Frostfell. For a history-loving painter, the White Dragon on the door made perfect sense.
Ivory opened the door and expected the usual mess. Paint splatters everywhere, brushes and paper scattered around the room, easels covering every inch of the wall. Unexpectedly, however, a different scene met her eyes. The entire room was clean, and before a background of red velvet stood a chair. On the chair sat Crown Prince Aquilo, who was just being painted.
“Good morning, Ivory! Would you like to watch as your future king is painted?” asked Aquilo and winked at Ivory.
„Excuse me, little prince“, said Ivory, mostly ignoring him and gathering the things the quiet princess wanted. „I'm only here to get art supplies.“
„My little girl wants to go already?“, asked Aquilo. „I want you to stay!“
„But I don't.“ Ivory found the art supplies on the list and put them in a box. „Besides, I'm not a girl.“
The prince was however of a different opinion. „Oh sweetie, that's just a phase! As you grow older, you'll grow out of it!“, he said vaguely.
„I have to go“, said Ivory and felt uncomfortable with the prince's answer. All the ugly remarks he and others had made about Ivory's gender identity in the past came flooding back. I just want to get away from here.
„You're leaving already?“ Suddenly the prince appeared at the door and ignored the loud protests of the royal painter.
„That's not behavior for a future king!“, said Ivory.
„No one will find out. The people won't believe you, and the painter will stay silent if his life is worth anything. He looked at the painter briefly and then leaned closer to Ivory. „What do you think of a date?“ Ivory had been bothered multiple times in the past, but never by a prince, let alone the crown prince.
„Do you even know what the word 'No' means?“, spat Ivory out and pushed the crown prince away.
„No“, answered Aquilo with a smile. Of course the crown prince, who can have anything he wants, doesn't know what the word 'No' means.
Ivory rolled her eyes. "Why would you want to go out with someone like me? You must have at least 100 admirers?"
"Actually, it's 50," interrupted him, still smiling. He pushed back his hair, which was swirling in the cold air.
"Now you get it! Why me? I'm a danger to the palace." Ivory crossed her arms.
"You are the most beautiful girl I have ever seen." Aquilo lifted Ivory's chin with his finger and forced her to look at him.
